The 1926–27 &lt;a href="British%20Home%20Championship"&gt;British Home Championship&lt;/a&gt; was a &lt;a href="football%20%28soccer%29"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; tournament played between the British &lt;a href="Home%20Nations"&gt;Home Nations&lt;/a&gt; during the 1926–27 season. It was shared by &lt;a href="England%20national%20football%20team"&gt;England&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Scotland%20national%20football%20team"&gt;Scotland&lt;/a&gt; after a series of high scoring draws in the opening matches left England, &lt;a href="Wales%20national%20football%20team"&gt;Wales&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Ireland%20national%20football%20team%20%281882%E2%80%931950%29"&gt;Ireland&lt;/a&gt; well behind with Scotland ahead, only for England to defeat Scotland in the deciding game with a late winning goal by &lt;a href="Dixie%20Dean"&gt;Dixie Dean&lt;/a&gt; – the first time the Scots had lost since 1924, and their first loss at home since 1906.
